article.description: — Darius Burford had a career-high 27 points as Elon easily defeated William & Mary 75-54 on Saturday.
article.headline: Burford carries Elon over William & Mary 75-54
article.linkText: Burford carries Elon over William & Mary 75-54
article.story: WILLIAMSBURG, Va. -- — Darius Burford had a career-high 27 points as Elon easily defeated William & Mary 75-54 on Saturday. Ikenna Ndugba added 20 points and eight rebounds for the Phoenix (5-8, 2-7 Colonial Athletic Association). Ndugba also had eight rebounds. Michael Graham had four blocks for Elon. Elon dominated the first half and led 44-23 at the break. The Phoenix’s 44 points in the first half were a season best for the team. Connor Kochera had 20 points for the Tribe (6-8, 4-5). Ben Wight added eight rebounds and three blocks. Luke Loewe, whose 17 points per game heading into the contest led the Tribe, had 5 points on 2-of-11 shooting. ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25 ------ This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
